When traveling with a baby in the New Year, I chose the CITIGO Tiananmen Square store. 1) Hotel location - the location is very good. At one end of Qianmen Street, it is very close to the Zhushikou subway station, and the five days in Beijing are basically subway travel. During the New Year, the restaurants are full. We can go to get the number first, then go back to the hotel to rest, and go to the restaurant later. This is very suitable for families with children who want to rest. It is also very convenient to walk to Tiananmen Square. There is a 24-hour convenience store next door to the hotel, which is very convenient for shopping. 2) Hotel facilities - the hotel seems to be remodeled from a private house, and the sound insulation is very poor. Basically, you can clearly hear the chatting and calling next door. Light sleepers had better ask if there is anyone living next door to the hotel before checking in. 3) Cleanliness of the hotel - frankly, cleanliness can only be described as passable. It may be due to the shortage of staff during the New Year, and the sewer smell is a bit strong. Everyone tolerated each other and it passed. 4) Hotel breakfast - because I referred to some other guests' comments before booking the hotel, I have some concerns about breakfast. In fact the shortage of staff during the new year did affect the breakfast. The lady at the front desk is responsible for checking in at the front desk, cleaning the dining table, making up meals in time, and so on. Really busy. Breakfast can only be said to be full, and an extra breakfast is 69 yuan.
